ny farms.\nCity green grocers are charging from\n15 to 25 cents for pumpkins, with\nhigher prices for unusually large\nones. Town dealers are stocking up\nfor Halloween.\nGrowers say the size of the crop\nshould be a factor In restoring the\n5-cent wedge of pie.\nOver 42,000 Depositors Capital and Surplus, $2,000,000\nMaking Pay Day Deposits\nof not a few\nDeposits Invited in Any Amount; Same Rate of\nInterest Paid on Small and Large Accounts\nOpen Until 5:30 P.M, Monday and Tuesday\nOFFICERS: DIRECTORS:\nWILLIAM D. HOOVER President Woodbury Blair William D. Hoot**\nj WOODBURY BLAIR ~..1at V. Prea. James A. Buchanan Reginald 8. Huidekoper\nPRANK W. STONE ....I\u2019d V. Pres. William A. H. Church Victor Kauffmann\n1 PRANK STETSON Truat Officer Walter O. Clephane Charlea Minahall\nCHAS. C. LAMBORN Treasurer U. Hosier Dulany, Jr. Edmund D. Rheeui\nB. PERCIVAL WILSON Secretary Wm. E. Edmonaton Frank Stetaon\nI F. R. XJLI.MER, Aunt. Sec. dc Aaet. Tr. Franklin H. Ellia Frank W. Stone\nBRUCE BAIRD .-Asat. Truat Officer Frederick A. Kenning William H. Walker\nj DAVID HORNET. .Aast. Trust Officer H. Prescott Gatley Henry K. Willard\nNational Savings Trust Co.\nj 56th Oldest Savings Depository in Washington\nYear Cor. 15th and New York Ave.\n\n______________________\nj\nIn the Path of\nWashington\u2019s Growth\nQUR First Mortgages owe their dou-\nble security to the impregnable\nsafety of Washington and our choice of\nvaluable, improved property in the path\nof the city\u2019s growth.\nEvery loan secured by our First Mort\ngage Notes holds a fifty to one hundred\nper cent margin of safety in the value\nof the property, and is arranged in short\nterms to permit periodical investigation.\nThese Notes are available in denomi\nnations of SIOO to SIOO,OOO, and may be\npurchased either for cash or through\nour plan of SYSTEM SAVING.\nCall or Write for Detailed Information\nSwartzell, Rheem Hensey Co.\n727 15th Street N.W.\n54 Years Without Loss to an Investor\nI\ni\ni\nI\u2018r j 